bush robin
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a small, round, tame and inquisitive little bird, one of the Petroica australis subspecies, known also as New Zealand robin.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Environment
Region: [none]
